; =============================================================
; STARTER PROTEIN DATABASE
; =============================================================
; CORRECTED per research: the evolutionary link to tRNase Z runs
; through METALLO-beta-lactamases (zinc-dependent, class B — e.g.
; NDM, VIM, IMP, L1), NOT serine beta-lactamases (class A — TEM,
; SHV, CTX-M) or class D (OXA). Both metallo-beta-lactamases and
; tRNase Z belong to the same ancient "MBL-fold" superfamily
; (Daiyasu et al. 2001; Kim et al. on PNGM-1). An earlier version
; of this file used TEM-1, which is a serine enzyme and NOT part
; of that shared-fold story — if you're comparing against older
; notes/screenshots, this is the fix.
;
; SPECIES NOTE: NDM-1 and its close relatives are most commonly found in
; Klebsiella pneumoniae, Escherichia coli, and Acinetobacter baumannii — use
; these three as your species set for a dataset that actually reflects where
; this resistance gene shows up clinically (see NDM Metallo-β-Lactamases
; review, PMC6431124, in your references).
; =============================================================

>LACTAMASE|Klebsiella_pneumoniae|blaNDM-1|C7C422 Metallo-beta-lactamase NDM-1, mature protein region 29-270 (real, UniProt)
GEIRPTIGQQMETGDQRFGDLVFRQLAPNVWQHTSYLDMPGFGAVASNGLIVRDGGRVLV
VDTAWTDDQTAQILNWIKQEINLPVALAVVTHAHQDKMGGMDALHAAGIATYANALSNQL
APQEGMVAAQHSLTFAANGWVEPATAPNFGPLKVFYPGPGHTSDNITVGIDGTDIAFGGC
LIKDSKAKSLGNLGDADTEHYAASARAFGAAFPKASMIVMSHSAPDSRAAITHTARMADK
LR

>LACTAMASE|Escherichia_coli|blaNDM-1_or_blaVIM|PLACEHOLDER Replace with an NDM or VIM-family metallo-beta-lactamase from E. coli (search UniProt: blaNDM AND organism E. coli)
MSIQHFRVALIPFFAAFCLPVFAHPETLVKVKDAEDQLGARVGYIELDLNSGKILESFRP
EERFPMMSTFKVLLCGAVLSRVDAGQEQLGRRIHYSQNDLVEYSPVTEKHLTDGMTVREL
CSAAITMSDNTAANLLLTTIGGPKELTAFLHNMGDHVTRLDRWEPELNEAIPNDERDTTM

